uc_aria is an example app using aria menus in a web2py application.

2010-01-05
- implemented menu/right_menu.html in aria. Seems to be working fine.
- removed access keys for the time being.

Instructions for creating the application

Views
=====

layout.html
-----------
around line 18 of layout.html insert {{include 'menu/aria_site_menu.html'}} just after the line <h3>{{=response.subtitle or ''}}</h3> as follows:

	{{include 'menu/aria_site_menu.html'}}

menu/aria\_site\_menu.html
------------------------
Create the file menu/aria\_site\_menu.html in the Views section and insert the following code. Eventually you may want to migrate out the CSS.

	<style type="text/css">
	h2.nav {
	position: absolute;
	top: -20em;
	left: -200em;
	}
	
	div#nav_aria li, h2 {
	display: inline;
	padding-left: 0.5em;
	background-repeat: no-repeat;
	background-position: left center;
	}
	
	div#nav_aria li.nobullet {
	background-image: none;
	}
	
	div#nav_aria a {
	padding: 0px;
	padding-right: 0.25em;
	padding-left: 0.25em;
	text-decoration: none;
	}
	
	div#nav_aria a:link, div#nav_aria a:visited {
	font-weight: bold;
	}
	
	div#nav_aria a:hover, div#nav_aria a:focus {
	color: #f5b673;
	background-color: rgb(56,56,73);
	}
	</style>
	
	<div id="nav_aria" style="text-align: right;">
	    <h2 class="nav" id="nav_aria_label">Site Menu</h2>
		<ul id="navigation1" role="navigation" aria-labelledby="nav_aria_label" tabindex="-1">
	        [<li><a href="{{=URL(r=request,c='default',f='index')}}">{{=T('main')}}</a></li>
			|<li><a href="{{=URL(r=request,c='news',f='news_index')}}">{{=T('news')}}</a></li>
			|<li><a href="{{=URL(r=request,c='language',f='aria_lang_index')}}">{{=T('language')}} : {{=session._language}}</a></li>
			{{pass}}
			{{if not session.authorized:}}
  	            |<li><a href="{{=URL(a='admin' ,c='default',f='site')}}">{{=T('admin')}}</a></li>]
			{{else:}}
				|<li><a href="{{=URL(a='admin' ,c='default',f='logout')}}">{{=T('admin_logout')}}</a></li>]
        {{pass}}
        </ul>
	</div>

